======================================================================
(8,1) GENERAL PROOF — DISJOINT PAIR DECOMPOSITION
======================================================================

--- Part 1: 5-cycle vertex set eliminates alpha_2=1 ---
  If A (5 vertices, d_5>=1) is disjoint from B (3 vertices, d=1):
  HYP-1104: d_5>=1 on A → t_3(A)>=3
  Each internal 3-cycle of A is disjoint from B
  alpha_2 >= t_3(A)*1 + d_5(A)*1 >= 3+1 = 4
  CONTRADICTION with alpha_2=1. ✓
  VERIFIED: d_5>=1 → t_3>=3 at n=5 (all 1024 tournaments)

